{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1080,"text":"The last time I heard my son's voice"},{"time":3600,"text":"was when he walked out the front door"},{"time":5960,"text":"on his way to school."},{"time":8480,"text":"He called out one word in the darkness:"},{"time":11320,"text":"\"Bye.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":13000,"text":"It was April 20, 1999."},{"time":16880,"text":"Later that morning,\nat Columbine High School,"},{"time":19960,"text":"my son Dylan and his friend Eric"},{"time":22920,"text":"killed 12 students and a teacher"},{"time":26280,"text":"and wounded more than 20 others\nbefore taking their own lives."},{"time":31160,"text":"Thirteen innocent people were killed,"},{"time":34240,"text":"leaving their loved ones\nin a state of grief and trauma."},{"time":38320,"text":"Others sustained injuries,"},{"time":40200,"text":"some resulting in disfigurement\nand permanent disability."},{"time":45840,"text":"But the enormity of the tragedy"},{"time":47680,"text":"can't be measured only by the number\nof deaths and injuries that took place."},{"time":52720,"text":"There's no way to quantify\nthe psychological damage"},{"time":56160,"text":"of those who were in the school,"},{"time":58120,"text":"or who took part\nin rescue or cleanup efforts."},{"time":62280,"text":"There's no way to assess\nthe magnitude of a tragedy like Columbine,"},{"time":66680,"text":"especially when it can be a blueprint"},{"time":68960,"text":"for other shooters who go on\nto commit atrocities of their own."},{"time":73600,"text":"Columbine was a tidal wave,"},{"time":76200,"text":"and when the crash ended,"},{"time":77480,"text":"it would take years\nfor the community and for society"},{"time":81440,"text":"to comprehend its impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84720,"text":"It has taken me years\nto try to accept my son's legacy."},{"time":89760,"text":"The cruel behavior\nthat defined the end of his life"},{"time":92920,"text":"showed me that he was a completely\ndifferent person from the one I knew."},{"time":97600,"text":"Afterwards people asked,"},{"time":100000,"text":"\"How could you not know?"},{"time":102560,"text":"What kind of a mother were you?\""},{"time":105240,"text":"I still ask myself those same questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109080,"text":"Before the shootings,\nI thought of myself as a good mom."},{"time":112760,"text":"Helping my children become caring,"},{"time":115240,"text":"healthy, responsible adults"},{"time":117600,"text":"was the most important role of my life."},{"time":121760,"text":"But the tragedy convinced me\nthat I failed as a parent,"},{"time":125840,"text":"and it's partially this sense of failure\nthat brings me here today."},{"time":131240,"text":"Aside from his father,"},{"time":132520,"text":"I was the one person\nwho knew and loved Dylan the most."},{"time":136800,"text":"If anyone could have known\nwhat was happening,"},{"time":139080,"text":"it should have been me, right?"},{"time":142000,"text":"But I didn't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145440,"text":"Today, I'm here to share the experience"},{"time":147360,"text":"of what it's like to be the mother\nof someone who kills and hurts."},{"time":152200,"text":"For years after the tragedy,\nI combed through memories,"},{"time":156080,"text":"trying to figure out\nexactly where I failed as a parent."},{"time":160280,"text":"But there are no simple answers."},{"time":163040,"text":"I can't give you any solutions."},{"time":165520,"text":"All I can do"},{"time":167760,"text":"is share what I have learned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171440,"text":"When I talk to people\nwho didn't know me before the shootings,"},{"time":175080,"text":"I have three challenges to meet."},{"time":177640,"text":"First, when I walk into a room like this,"},{"time":181480,"text":"I never know if someone there\nhas experienced loss"},{"time":185080,"text":"because of what my son did."},{"time":188080,"text":"I feel a need to acknowledge the suffering\ncaused by a member of my family"},{"time":192240,"text":"who isn't here to do it for himself."},{"time":195080,"text":"So first, with all of my heart,"},{"time":198320,"text":"I'm sorry if my son has caused you pain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203640,"text":"The second challenge I have"},{"time":206040,"text":"is that I must ask for understanding\nand even compassion"},{"time":210560,"text":"when I talk about\nmy son's death as a suicide."},{"time":214480,"text":"Two years before he died,"},{"time":216640,"text":"he wrote on a piece of paper in a notebook"},{"time":218880,"text":"that he was cutting himself."},{"time":221200,"text":"He said that he was in agony"},{"time":222840,"text":"and wanted to get a gun\nso he could end his life."},{"time":226160,"text":"I didn't know about any of this\nuntil months after his death."},{"time":230720,"text":"When I talk about his death as a suicide,"},{"time":234160,"text":"I'm not trying to downplay the viciousness\nhe showed at the end of his life."},{"time":238840,"text":"I'm trying to understand"},{"time":240840,"text":"how his suicidal thinking"},{"time":242960,"text":"led to murder."},{"time":245080,"text":"After a lot of reading\nand talking with experts,"},{"time":248320,"text":"I have come to believe"},{"time":250000,"text":"that his involvement in the shootings\nwas rooted not in his desire to kill"},{"time":255480,"text":"but in his desire to die."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258320,"text":"The third challenge I have\nwhen I talk about my son's murder-suicide"},{"time":263640,"text":"is that I'm talking about mental health --"},{"time":267680,"text":"excuse me --"},{"time":268920,"text":"is that I'm talking about mental health,"},{"time":271560,"text":"or brain health, as I prefer to call it,\nbecause it's more concrete."},{"time":275760,"text":"And in the same breath,\nI'm talking about violence."},{"time":279520,"text":"The last thing I want to do\nis to contribute to the misunderstanding"},{"time":283120,"text":"that already exists around mental illness."},{"time":286360,"text":"Only a very small percent of those\nwho have a mental illness"},{"time":291160,"text":"are violent toward other people,"},{"time":294800,"text":"but of those who die by suicide,"},{"time":297960,"text":"it's estimated that about 75\nto maybe more than 90 percent"},{"time":302200,"text":"have a diagnosable\nmental health condition of some kind."},{"time":306680,"text":"As you all know very well,"},{"time":307960,"text":"our mental health care system\nis not equipped to help everyone,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and not everyone with destructive thoughts"},{"time":314520,"text":"fits the criteria"},{"time":316280,"text":"for a specific diagnosis."},{"time":319200,"text":"Many who have ongoing feelings"},{"time":321240,"text":"of fear or anger or hopelessness"},{"time":325000,"text":"are never assessed or treated."},{"time":327640,"text":"Too often, they get our attention\nonly if they reach a behavioral crisis."},{"time":333400,"text":"If estimates are correct"},{"time":335480,"text":"that about one\nto two percent of all suicides"},{"time":338440,"text":"involves the murder of another person,"},{"time":342080,"text":"when suicide rates rise,\nas they are rising for some populations,"},{"time":346720,"text":"the murder-suicide rates\nwill rise as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350520,"text":"I wanted to understand what was going on\nin Dylan's mind prior to his death,"},{"time":356040,"text":"so I looked for answers\nfrom other survivors of suicide loss."},{"time":361640,"text":"I did research and volunteered\nto help with fund-raising events,"},{"time":366200,"text":"and whenever I could,"},{"time":368000,"text":"I talked with those who had\nsurvived their own suicidal crisis"},{"time":372520,"text":"or attempt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374840,"text":"One of the most helpful\nconversations I had"},{"time":377080,"text":"was with a coworker"},{"time":378560,"text":"who overheard me talking to someone else"},{"time":380489,"text":"in my office cubicle."},{"time":382760,"text":"She heard me say\nthat Dylan could not have loved me"},{"time":386200,"text":"if he could do something\nas horrible as he did."},{"time":390000,"text":"Later, when she found me alone,"},{"time":392760,"text":"she apologized for overhearing\nthat conversation,"},{"time":395240,"text":"but told me that I was wrong."},{"time":397880,"text":"She said that when she was\na young, single mother"},{"time":400520,"text":"with three small children,"},{"time":402600,"text":"she became severely depressed\nand was hospitalized to keep her safe."},{"time":408000,"text":"At the time, she was certain"},{"time":410320,"text":"that her children\nwould be better off if she died,"},{"time":413600,"text":"so she had made a plan to end her life."},{"time":416880,"text":"She assured me that a mother's love\nwas the strongest bond on Earth,"},{"time":420960,"text":"and that she loved her children\nmore than anything in the world,"},{"time":424640,"text":"but because of her illness,"},{"time":426880,"text":"she was sure that they\nwould be better off without her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431680,"text":"What she said and what\nI've learned from others"},{"time":434080,"text":"is that we do not make\nthe so-called decision or choice"},{"time":438840,"text":"to die by suicide"},{"time":440440,"text":"in the same way\nthat we choose what car to drive"},{"time":443320,"text":"or where to go on a Saturday night."},{"time":446360,"text":"When someone is\nin an extremely suicidal state,"},{"time":449480,"text":"they are in a stage four\nmedical health emergency."},{"time":454680,"text":"Their thinking is impaired and they've\nlost access to tools of self-governance."},{"time":460320,"text":"Even though they can\nmake a plan and act with logic,"},{"time":463520,"text":"their sense of truth\nis distorted by a filter of pain"},{"time":467480,"text":"through which they\ninterpret their reality."},{"time":470880,"text":"Some people can be very good\nat hiding this state,"},{"time":474560,"text":"and they often have\ngood reasons for doing that."},{"time":478840,"text":"Many of us have\nsuicidal thoughts at some point,"},{"time":482040,"text":"but persistent,\nongoing thoughts of suicide"},{"time":485560,"text":"and devising a means to die"},{"time":487800,"text":"are symptoms of pathology,"},{"time":490160,"text":"and like many illnesses,"},{"time":492080,"text":"the condition has to be\nrecognized and treated"},{"time":495520,"text":"before a life is lost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498600,"text":"But my son's death\nwas not purely a suicide."},{"time":502200,"text":"It involved mass murder."},{"time":505080,"text":"I wanted to know how his\nsuicidal thinking became homicidal."},{"time":511920,"text":"But research is sparse\nand there are no simple answers."},{"time":516240,"text":"Yes, he probably had ongoing depression."},{"time":520679,"text":"He had a personality\nthat was perfectionistic and self-reliant,"},{"time":527120,"text":"and that made him less likely\nto seek help from others."},{"time":531880,"text":"He had experienced\ntriggering events at the school"},{"time":535360,"text":"that left him feeling\ndebased and humiliated and mad."},{"time":542160,"text":"And he had a complicated friendship"},{"time":545440,"text":"with a boy who shared his feelings\nof rage and alienation,"},{"time":549800,"text":"and who was seriously disturbed,"},{"time":552920,"text":"controlling and homicidal."},{"time":556280,"text":"And on top of this period in his life"},{"time":559160,"text":"of extreme vulnerability and fragility,"},{"time":563280,"text":"Dylan found access to guns"},{"time":565680,"text":"even though we'd never\nowned any in our home."},{"time":568800,"text":"It was appallingly easy\nfor a 17-year-old boy to buy guns,"},{"time":574040,"text":"both legally and illegally,\nwithout my permission or knowledge."},{"time":579880,"text":"And somehow, 17 years\nand many school shootings later,"},{"time":585080,"text":"it's still appallingly easy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589160,"text":"What Dylan did that day broke my heart,"},{"time":593240,"text":"and as trauma so often does,"},{"time":595120,"text":"it took a toll on my body and on my mind."},{"time":599360,"text":"Two years after the shootings,\nI got breast cancer,"},{"time":603200,"text":"and two years after that,\nI began to have mental health problems."},{"time":608480,"text":"On top of the constant, perpetual grief"},{"time":611920,"text":"I was terrified that I would run\ninto a family member"},{"time":615520,"text":"of someone Dylan had killed,"},{"time":617600,"text":"or be accosted by the press"},{"time":620000,"text":"or by an angry citizen."},{"time":622920,"text":"I was afraid to turn on the news,"},{"time":625520,"text":"afraid to hear myself being called\na terrible parent or a disgusting person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633320,"text":"I started having panic attacks."},{"time":637240,"text":"The first bout started\nfour years after the shootings,"},{"time":641440,"text":"when I was getting ready\nfor the depositions"},{"time":644000,"text":"and would have to meet\nthe victims' families face to face."},{"time":647600,"text":"The second round started\nsix years after the shootings,"},{"time":651000,"text":"when I was preparing\nto speak publicly about murder-suicide"},{"time":654480,"text":"for the first time at a conference."},{"time":657520,"text":"Both episodes lasted several weeks."},{"time":662160,"text":"The attacks happened everywhere:"},{"time":664320,"text":"in the hardware store, in my office,"},{"time":667640,"text":"or even while reading a book in bed."},{"time":670600,"text":"My mind would suddenly lock\ninto this spinning cycle of terror"},{"time":675680,"text":"and no matter how I hard I tried"},{"time":677800,"text":"to calm myself down\nor reason my way out of it,"},{"time":681880,"text":"I couldn't do it."},{"time":684440,"text":"It felt as if my brain\nwas trying to kill me,"},{"time":687920,"text":"and then, being afraid of being afraid"},{"time":690520,"text":"consumed all of my thoughts."},{"time":693200,"text":"That's when I learned firsthand"},{"time":695120,"text":"what it feels like\nto have a malfunctioning mind,"},{"time":698640,"text":"and that's when I truly\nbecame a brain health advocate."},{"time":703760,"text":"With therapy and medication and self-care,"},{"time":706760,"text":"life eventually returned"},{"time":708600,"text":"to whatever could be thought of\nas normal under the circumstances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713240,"text":"When I looked back\non all that had happened,"},{"time":715320,"text":"I could see that my son's\nspiral into dysfunction"},{"time":719680,"text":"probably occurred\nover a period of about two years,"},{"time":723200,"text":"plenty of time to get him help,"},{"time":726280,"text":"if only someone had known\nthat he needed help"},{"time":729320,"text":"and known what to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735680,"text":"Every time someone asks me,"},{"time":738280,"text":"\"How could you not have known?\","},{"time":740760,"text":"it feels like a punch in the gut."},{"time":743840,"text":"It carries accusation\nand taps into my feelings of guilt"},{"time":748400,"text":"that no matter how much therapy I've had"},{"time":750920,"text":"I will never fully eradicate."},{"time":753880,"text":"But here's something I've learned:"},{"time":756720,"text":"if love were enough"},{"time":758600,"text":"to stop someone who is suicidal"},{"time":760760,"text":"from hurting themselves,"},{"time":763000,"text":"suicides would hardly ever happen."},{"time":766320,"text":"But love is not enough,"},{"time":769240,"text":"and suicide is prevalent."},{"time":771680,"text":"It's the second leading cause of death"},{"time":774520,"text":"for people age 10 to 34,"},{"time":777640,"text":"and 15 percent of American youth"},{"time":780320,"text":"report having made a suicide plan"},{"time":783080,"text":"in the last year."},{"time":786160,"text":"I've learned that no matter\nhow much we want to believe we can,"},{"time":791000,"text":"we cannot know or control"},{"time":793840,"text":"everything our loved ones think and feel,"},{"time":796760,"text":"and the stubborn belief\nthat we are somehow different,"},{"time":800560,"text":"that someone we love\nwould never think of hurting themselves"},{"time":804000,"text":"or someone else,"},{"time":806080,"text":"can cause us to miss"},{"time":808120,"text":"what's hidden in plain sight."},{"time":811840,"text":"And if worst case scenarios\ndo come to pass,"},{"time":816520,"text":"we'll have to learn\nto forgive ourselves for not knowing"},{"time":820440,"text":"or for not asking the right questions"},{"time":823160,"text":"or not finding the right treatment."},{"time":827240,"text":"We should always assume"},{"time":828520,"text":"that someone we love may be suffering,"},{"time":831880,"text":"regardless of what they say"},{"time":834520,"text":"or how they act."},{"time":836720,"text":"We should listen with our whole being,"},{"time":839800,"text":"without judgments,"},{"time":841680,"text":"and without offering solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847360,"text":"I know that I will live with this tragedy,"},{"time":850600,"text":"with these multiple tragedies,"},{"time":852560,"text":"for the rest of my life."},{"time":855320,"text":"I know that in the minds of many,"},{"time":861080,"text":"what I lost can't compare\nto what the other families lost."},{"time":866240,"text":"I know my struggle\ndoesn't make theirs any easier."},{"time":871000,"text":"I know there are even some who think\nI don't have the right to any pain,"},{"time":876400,"text":"but only to a life of permanent penance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881800,"text":"In the end what I know comes down to this:"},{"time":885320,"text":"the tragic fact is that even\nthe most vigilant and responsible of us"},{"time":891520,"text":"may not be able to help,"},{"time":894840,"text":"but for love's sake,"},{"time":897040,"text":"we must never stop trying"},{"time":899240,"text":"to know the unknowable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901560,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902800,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}